    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><verbatim>    Parser element for decimal fraction literals.

    Usage examples:
    &gt;&gt;&gt; from dragonfly.parser import Parser
    &gt;&gt;&gt; parser = Parser(Float())
    &gt;&gt;&gt; parser.parse(&quot;0.0&quot;)
    0.0
    &gt;&gt;&gt; parser.parse(&quot;.000&quot;)
    0.0
    &gt;&gt;&gt; parser.parse(&quot;-.0&quot;)
    0.0
    &gt;&gt;&gt; parser.parse(&quot;1.0&quot;)
    1.0
    &gt;&gt;&gt; parser.parse(&quot;-1.0&quot;)
    -1.0
    &gt;&gt;&gt; parser.parse(&quot;-1.75&quot;)
    -1.75</verbatim> </para>    </detaileddescription>
